gomodel:SYNGO_748  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0098993 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: Complexin-3 is expressed in different brain regions in rat (Fig.2B, 3) and mice (3D).\n\nSubcellular fractionation demonstrates the presence of Complexin-3 in the cytosolic synaptic fraction (LS2, comparable to Complexin-1/2), but is is also enriched in the light membrane pellet (P3), but also detectable in the crude synaptic vesicular fraction (LP2), and in synaptic membranes (LP1 and SPM; Fig. 3 E).\n\nIn the retina, Complexin-3 co-localizes with the presynaptic SV marker VgluT1 in the inner plexiform layer (rod bipolar cells, IHC, Fig.4). Complexin-3 is farnesylated at the CAAX-box motifs at their COOH terminus (HEK cell assay, Fig.5). In comparison to Complexin-1/2, overexpressed, farnesylated Complexin-3 is localized to synapses in mouse hippocampal cultures (colocalized with the SV marker synaptophysin by ICC). Overexpression of a mutated Complexin-3 variant that cannot be farnesylated, is diffusely distributed throughout the neuron like Complexin-1/2 (Fig. 7).\n\nPolyclonal antisera directed against CPXs III and IV were generated with His-tagged fusion proteins as antigens (Eurogentech). There is cross-reactivity of the antibody between Complexin-3 and -4, but only Complexin-3 is expressed in the brain (Fig.3B).\n\n21/8/2017 Pim\nIn Fig.8 Complexin-3 is shown to be able to rescue a Complexin-1/2 DKO phenotype, which adds to the inference of SV and plasma membrane localization (this is wherer SV fusion takes place). Experimental description: Rat and mouse:\ncDNA: Using primers designed on the basis of the human cDNA sequences of CPXs III and IV, the corresponding mouse cDNAs were amplified from mouse brain QUICK-Clone cDNA ...\nNorthern blots: Rat multiple tissue RNA blots (CLONTECH Laboratories, Inc.) were used...\nrat cortex subcellular fractions...\nmouse neuron cultures - (Dresbach et al., 2003; PMID: 12812759)..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_748" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

